From 416975f8b3115de5d2a767c5d21695c738ae56dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shawn Rutledge <shawn.rutledge@qt.io>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 10:58:38 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] QWaylandTextInputv3: don't warn on leave for a destroyed
 surface
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When a surface is destroyed while text input is active, the compositor
sends a zwp_text_input_v3.leave event. By the time it is dispatched on
the client side, the wl_surface proxy may already have been freed, so
the surface argument arrives as nullptr. This is normal teardown; treat
it as such rather than logging a spurious warning.

The same issue existed in disableSurface() and was fixed by
e992607d50ed7a13f4e484dbcd1aaa78b53044e1. The leave() handler had an
identical pattern that the original fix did not address — in qtwayland
the two warnings were separate methods and only disableSurface() was
cleaned up. This commit fixes the surviving warning in leave().

Task-number: QTBUG-120533
Pick-to: 6.10
Assisted-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
Change-Id: Ifac7fd4b56fd1ade1b7fbe373df37c4e708e7ae7
Reviewed-by: David Edmundson <davidedmundson@kde.org>
(cherry picked from commit ac8b2e9b40bf19aa889345f7b617392bef906040)
Reviewed-by: Qt Cherry-pick Bot <cherrypick_bot@qt-project.org>
---
 src/plugins/platforms/wayland/qwaylandtextinputv3.cpp | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/plugins/platforms/wayland/qwaylandtextinputv3.cpp b/src/plugins/platforms/wayland/qwaylandtextinputv3.cpp
index cacb70faf59..b271fe10441 100644
--- a/src/plugins/platforms/wayland/qwaylandtextinputv3.cpp
+++ b/src/plugins/platforms/wayland/qwaylandtextinputv3.cpp
@@ -80,7 +80,9 @@ void QWaylandTextInputv3::zwp_text_input_v3_leave(struct ::wl_surface *surface)
     if (!m_surface)
         return; // Nothing to leave
 
-    if (m_surface != surface)
+    // surface == nullptr means the wl_surface proxy was already freed (surface destroyed
+    // before the leave event was dispatched); treat it as normal teardown, not a mismatch.
+    if (surface && m_surface != surface)
         qCWarning(qLcQpaWaylandTextInput()) << Q_FUNC_INFO << "Got leave event for surface" << surface << "with focusing surface" << m_surface;
 
     m_currentPreeditString.clear();
